The paper deals with physical layer caching in wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed framework involves joint optimization of cache content placement and content delivery, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The use of MIMO technology and cooperative networks is also mentioned, which relates to multimedia (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
